FTP (File Transfer Protocol)
• FTP (File Transfer Protocol) is a standard network protocol used to transfer files between a client and a server over a TCP/IP network, such as the internet.

FTP Uses Two Ports :
Port 21 (Control Port)
• Used for command and control communication between the FTP client and server.
• Handles commands such as ls, pwd, cd, get, put, etc.
• Establishes and maintains the FTP session.

Port 20 (Data Port)
• Used for data transfer.
• Handles: File uploads and downloads
           Directory listings
           Other data communication
